==Old English==
===Etymology 1===
From Germanic; cognate with Old Norse [[hríð]].

====Pronunciation====
[[IPA]]: /hɹi:θ/

====Noun====
'''hrīþ''' ''f''
# a [[snowstorm]]; a [[storm]] or [[tempest]]
#:''hrið hreosende hrusan bindeð'': the falling snowstorm binds the earth.  (''The Wanderer'')

===Etymology 2===
From Germanic ''*xriþ-''.  Cognate with Old High German [[rito]].  Perhaps ultimately from the same source as Welsh [[cryd]].

====Pronunciation====
[[IPA]]: /hɹɪθ/

====Noun====
'''hriþ''' ''m''
# a [[fever]]

